                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Outer Mongolia/30: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-21T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 21, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 21—8:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>79. Following telegram has been received from the Consul General at Harbin: <pb
                        facs="0482" n="370" xml:id="pg_370"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“43. October 21, 6 p.m. The Soviet Consul General informed me today that
                            according to an accurate press despatch received by him from Moscow,
                            Kanki of the ‘Manchukuo’ delegation at Manchuli has informed the Outer
                            Mongolian delegation that if the refusal to accept a ‘Manchukuo’
                            diplomatic representative at Urga remains unaltered, an expedition will
                            be despatched to establish one by force.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
